                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is what I posted on the Summit boards (while I didn't go into full blow explainations, I did direct them to this area and I'm aware that it is being read.)
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">"Enchanters and the new Charm" 
<br />

<br />
There are some excellent points being made on The Runes boards. 
<br />
 
<br />
I'm going to be contacting Kandyman ( enchanter correspondent ) and seeing if together we can get a round table with a Developer and a handful of enchanters to discuss possible solutions. (If there is no way that will happen, someone please let me know so I can stop putting effort in that direction!) 
<br />
 
<br />
There just seems to be a whole lot of down sides to the change yet none of the prior penatlies have been removed. In OOW the pets are MUCH weaker, much less beneficial. Shouldn't the penalties be removed or something to balance it back out?
<br />
 
<br />
While I understand and agree that Enchanters were too powerful at one time because of charm, it certainly seems the scale has tipped very far in the other direction.  Are you sure that DPS is what it was intended to be?? Less than half seems a bit extreme. Is it intended that immediatly upon break the mob returns to original DPS ? 
<br />
 
<br />
If nothing else will someone direct a Developer to: <a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewforum.php?f=28" target="_blank">http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewforum.php?f=28</a> ? There are some great solutions being proposed, as well as more elequent explainations of why Enchanters are so upset</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
This was my response:
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: darkblue">Howdy Juwel,
<br />
 
<br />
I understand that many enchanters are upset about this change to the way the spell works on Omens mobs and I can understand why.  However, this is a change to the omens mobs only, not a nerf to enchanters overall (as many are saying).  The fact that an enchanter's charmed pet could do more dps than half a group was never an intended function of charm.  Mobs have and will continue to scale in power faster than PCs.  They have to do so to keep the game challenging.  In order to even allow the use of charm against the more powerful npcs, we had to have some scaling.  
<br />
 
<br />
Now, risk VS reward has come up many times during the enchanters debate over this issue, the risk has stayed the same as it has been, that monster is going to put a beat down on you when it regains its senses, however the reward was inordinately high.  We have fixed that.  For the risk of having an add that can lay some smack down, which is always a risk and not an added risk by any means, you got to do a crazy amount of DPS.  Now you get to still do a crazy amount of DPS, but granted half of what it was before (which is still pretty close to 2 rogues bashing on the beasty) and the risk is exactly the same, which again is the same risk you face when just normal hunting, that you have an add, the same risk you face when someone breaks mez for that matter.  
<br />
 
<br />
So perhaps the fault lays with us for allowing you to have that crazy DPS for so long in other zones, but now we have had to decide if we can let it continue as the mobs get tougher and we have decided that we cannot.   We had to change it and enchanters may not see it this way now but it is for the good of the game. 
<br />
Brenlo Bixiebopper
<br />
Community Relations Manager</span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
So there ya go.. I'm still hoping that with enough feedback, perhaps a helping hand from Kandyman, they will be at least open to listening to some type of compromise. So everyone please /feedback when you get a chance.
<br />

<br />
EDIT! - Oh also.. when some of you who parse everything get a chance.. please post what you have. I'd like to confirm that the DPS is what they say it is.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Quote of the Week:</span> 
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">"I'm very tempted to downgrade items and get a delightful orb of forgotten magic so that I can walk around with "blue balls" "</span>
<br />
Ejryuu of the <span style="font-weight: bold">Original</span> Runes.net
<br />

