                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As far as I can tell, they are equating risk with a non-hasted DWing add, and equating reward with a hasted, DWing pet.
<br />

<br />
Take a 150 DPS pet that doesn't Dual Wield naturally.
<br />

<br />
Give it 2 weapons, 36% item haste, 68% spell haste.
<br />

<br />
It now does 540 DPS.  Aka DPS of two rogues.
<br />

<br />
When it breaks, it magically becomes "just another add", not a dual-wielding beast of instant death to whoever aggroes it.
<br />

<br />
There are a few problems with this.
<br />

<br />
1&gt; Most mobs that can be made to DW in OoW seem to DW naturally (confirm?).  So that 540 DPS is now 300 DPS.
<br />
2&gt; They seem to be equating fully geared and hasted DPS for benefit, and unbuffed DPS for cost.
<br />
3&gt; They are ignoring the 33% Xp penalty.  So that 300 DPS is really worse than 200 DPS for xp purpose.
<br />
4&gt; They seem to think that having a snarer, stunner and extra healing around is free, and nobody else is giving up DPS for the extra pet DPS.
<br />

<br />
Of course, brenlo doesn't know all that much about EQ mechanics.  So by "they" I mean "the words brenlo is relaying to us".
<br />

<br />
This is becoming a silly game of telephone.  The Powers that Be relay their thoughts to Brenlo who relays it to somebody in the Enchanter community (Kandy, Juwel, Nany) who relays it to us, each step making the explanations and communications less sensicle.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
