                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I really like EQ but I have to say it doesn't look like I have much of a future as a chanter. I don't see the point in paying to sit around for hours buffing people and slowing if there's no shammy in my group. And that's pretty much all that's left at this point.
<br />
I was really resistant to buying OoW but I went ahead and got it because I thought maybe they'd have done a better job than they did on GoD but I wish I hadn't bothered. I'm not so much angry as just dissapointed. <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I'd like to point out that I get tons of aggro from just tashing and slowing. I don't see anyone balancing that. I'm the world's punching bag and I don't get HP or AC like a warrior. Setting an insanely angry mob on me with full dps after charm has suddenly broken isn't balanced at all. I'm risking death every time I charm something. I stopped doing GoD trials after the first couple weeks GoD was out cause I just couldn't survive my pet breaks. I died 11 times to a pooka in one morning. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />
<br />
I'd say if you're going to do it that way give me a self heal spell as compensation. I die most of the time before the healer can get a heal off anyway. I have no way of healing if something beats through my runes and at this lvl they can do that in 2-3 hits.
<br />

<br />
If we can't have mez and charm at the same time just give us one or the other. Don't take away the 2 spell lines that make us a unique class. It's like taking summoned pets away from mages, or nukes away from wizzies. In the right setting we can be balanced without nerfing us. So rather than nerfing us stop being lazy and go create scenarios where we can use our ablities.
<br />
Make places where mez is needed and give necros/bards mezzes that can be used there if a chanter isn't present. Make mobs that are randomly immune to snare/root/stun, make mobs that can't be hasted, make mobs that are designed to be used as weak dps DC'd pets, not something that's a wimp against another mob but can beat the crud out of me in less time than it takes to read the charm break message.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
