                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">However, this is a change to the omens mobs only, not a nerf to enchanters overall (as many are saying).</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And where are we supposed to play at level 70?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">For the risk of having an add that can lay some smack down, which is always a risk and not an added risk by any means...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This is almost mind-boggling. A charm break is just like an add? Come on...
<br />

<br />
1) The break can happen at literally any time and with no warning. Adds usually come with pulls, and wanderers can usually be spotted ahead of time. That awareness makes them much easier to deal with. I suppose it's like sitting on a spawn point, which is why people try to avoid that.
<br />

<br />
2) After a break the pet makes a beeline for the most vulnerable person in the group.
<br />

<br />
3) The insane pet DPS he complains about only comes by signicantly increasing the mob's normal DPS, making a break much more dangerous than an add.
<br />

<br />
4) Even if charm breaks were like adds, having a pet along that will break charm regularly would be like intentionally getting more adds. Of course it's an added risk.
<br />

<br />
I'm sure people can add more.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Now you get to still do a crazy amount of DPS, but granted half of what it was before</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
No, significantly less than half, especially against tougher mobs (i.e. the ones we'll spend most of our time fighting when we're all 70).
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">(which is still pretty close to 2 rogues bashing on the beasty)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Gentlemen, start your parsers. Shouldn't take long to debunk this.
<br />

<br />
(By the way, I presume it's always rogues since they're supposed to be the top DPS class.)
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">...the risk is exactly the same, which again is the same risk you face when just normal hunting, that you have an add, the same risk you face when someone breaks mez for that matter. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Okay, it is more like a broken mez, in that the enchanter gets aggro. Of course that's why if someone repeatedly subjects us to that risk we eventually kick them out of the group.
<br />

<br />
The risk is the same, the reward is down by 50-70% depending on the mob. You're seriously saying the reward was 2-3 times what it should have been and you're just getting around to fixing it now? It's not like this is a new problem--it's been like this ever since PoP at least. Was it unbalanced? Yes, and I don't mind that you want to fix it. But it couldn't have been that bad if you let it go for literally years.
<br />

<br />
The reality is that this nerf is so extreme, charm simply isn't viable in OoW. I know I've dropped it from my set of standard tactics. Maybe there will be the odd situation where it will come in handy, but there are a whole lot of tricks people use in odd situations that are completely useless 99% of the time.
<br />

<br />
I can understand why they want to reign in pet DPS. But there is a serious risk that enchanters will be both unneeded and no fun to play in today's content. Groups will simply find a half-decent puller so they don't need CC, pick up KEI from a buff bot, and replace us with a beastlord if they need slow and that proverbial rogue if they don't. MAYBE they'll lose some DPS, but the rogue is risk-free. And even if we do get a group, buff, slow, nuke, repeat is simply not a game I want to play. Nor have I found any other class that's much better, so if things do get this bad I won't be switching to an alt.
<br />

<br />
So what's to be done? Assuming that it's final that pet DPS will not be increased, the risk simply has to go down or you might as well get rid of charm entirely in OoW. Ex-pets killing the enchanter has to be rare and ex-pets wiping groups almost unheard of or a charm that does barely more DPS than a rogue won't be used (if it works out that people who are good at charm can make the risk acceptable and those who aren't can't, that would be okay, but that's not where we are now).
<br />

<br />
Or make CC viable again. Even if it's just in a few zones (I dragged groups to Seb well into the PoP era just because it was fun). Increase those aggro radii. Add more wanderers. If gets to the point where groups won't go to a zone or two without an enchanter, so be it! How many places "require" a cleric after all? But there are so many alternative forms of crowd control now, and rightly so, that there's little risk of us ever becoming part of a holy trinity again.
<br />

<br />
/sigh...I almost got myself excited there. Then I proofread my message and the Brenlo quotes I included, and that got me back to Brenlo's complete message. Not much hope there.
<br />

<br />
Good for the game? Maybe. But then, would it be good for the game if enchanters simply disappeared entirely? It sure would make designing encounters easier. Add a few NPC KEI casters and no one would even miss us in most places. Or just change our name to buffbot, change our description to note that we are not meant to be played as a primary character, and to give people a goal make some major raid loot that makes KEI last even longer.
<br />

<br />
Oh wait...
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
